<br>
Somehow I'm getting quoted and my quotes are being taken out of context big time. In no way do I support the idea of begging. It's disgusting to me, even if it's begging from a guard. It's the one skill I've never even thought to add to my ability. <br>
<br>
What I said to the original poster in my post was instead of begging for free items, ask for some advice. period. <br>
<br>
I wouldn't mind if someone asks for advice from me at 54. If I'm standing in Gfay and some new character can't find the bank in Kelethin I'll help him find it. I'm not afraid he'll grow up and KS my ragefire. I'm not saying anyone owes anyone an answer but asking for advice on how to do it yourself is different than begging for free stuff. I also said that they shouldn't bug a busy person for this.<br>
<br>
Then my next post had me saying that BoW DOES have Skill to go along with level, in response to someone saying the only reason they can raid anything is because of level.<br>
<br>
I don't know how it got twisted into me thinking they didn't. I said very specifically that they have developed skills and strategies that will work at all levels, I guess I needed to add that it will work for all levels on Level appropriate MoBs more explicitly. I wish you'd actually read my post if you want to quote and slam me for it. <br>
<br>
I can understand your post about competition and I kinda agree with you. You earn what you work for.<br>
<br>
Asdar Asprinicillin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#B8C0C7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/uborzak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>borzak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>1-60 unguilded or bust! </span><br>  Posts: 190<br> <font color=#122950>(1/30/02 11:30:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ftorvonnilousgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4414.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An idea to help out the smaller guilds.</span><hr size=1> Contrary to popular belief you're not really entitled to anything in EQ, except possibly a harassment free game evniroment.<br>
<br>
If you want what X guild has there's a simple solution. You get 40-50 people who play a lot, that pay attention, and have DESIRE.<br>
<br>
Then you start small and work hard. You do planes for armor, then kael for armor, you work for the betterment of the GUILD along the way. One you got Y equipment you work on new tactics on a new zone. Then move into that zone and farm X eqiupment all over to move onto the next zone, the whole time having a plan and refining it as you go. You just don't log on one day and say I think I'll powerlvl to 60 and get 40 peope like me to kill Vulak.<br>
<br>
